node.text: Some Friday thoughts....✨The greatest thing that comes along with age is feeling truly comfortable in your skin. 💫 Getting to know who you really are takes time! I would have never guessed it could take 3 decades but I’m grateful for every part of that evolution. ✨ And through every stage, the ice and skating has been there for me. During good or bad times, it was always “home” and always will be. It’s also where I’ve never felt out of place. Life throws a lot at you and to find a space where you feel whole and free is something I will never take for granted. 💫 I still look forward to many more years of learning and growing....all while having my “home” to escape to. 📽 @carlottaedwards #lakeskating #alberta #lakelouise #figureskating #banff #outdoorskating

node.text:
I have ALWAYS wanted to skate on an outdoor lake. Especially Lake Louise. 🧊✔️ So lucky for these few minutes of improv surrounded by this crazy beautiful scenery. After a long day of shooting and shivering from the cold, I got lost in my favorite little world and got to do what I love most. 🙌🏻 The ice started melting the day before we arrived but slushy, rutted and bumpy ice didn’t scare me. ⚔️ (Maybe it did a little, definitely not use to that but walked away in one piece. So it was more than worth it!) I’m thankful @carlottaedwards said “Quick, before we run to our next location - Skate for a minute! You will want to remember this”  She was so right! She is also so good behind a 🎥 @arianagrande 

#outdoorskating #lakelouise #lakelouisecanada #banff #alberta #iceskating #lakeskating #canada #figureskating #arianagrande #frozenlake #lakeskating

node.text: On this day my dream came true💫 4 minutes changed my life forever and in those 4 minutes I felt so many emotions. I felt immense nerves and pressure but the only emotion I really remember is pure joy. I loved every single second of being out there. Every skater knows the magic of a performance where everything falls into place and you feel like you’re flying. Goodness I love this sport so much. #olympics #figureskating

node.text: It was so great having @hollyhollisstars in town this week. We met through an Insta message from her bestie @elarha ✨ that turned into a video message I sent Holly which turned into friendship I’m so grateful to have.✨ Holly is the definition of a warrior. She also is a beautiful and kind human that can’t help but put a smile on your face. She embodies strength in every single way and inspires me so much. She has been fighting triple negative breast cancer for a few years now and her journey has not been easy, please send all the prayers and positive thoughts her way as she begins a new clinical trial. @hollyhollisstars ❤️

node.text: Strange that this isn’t my view anymore but I feel so grateful for my month long Olympic experience. As I was pulling out of LAX today, I was feeling a bit nostalgic and blue that it’s all over. But then I saw an athlete with a gold medal hanging around her neck pulling her luggage to the curb. I gave her a big wave and her beaming smile said it all. I don’t know her exact story but I know it was years of hard work and sacrifice behind the hardware she was now wearing. That snap shot stuck with me all day. The Olympics may be over but these athletes lives are changed forever. It’s never really over. I’m so grateful these Games actually took place and athletes like the one I saw today, could have their dreams realized. 🥇#olympics #tokyo2020 #tokyoolympics

node.text: This Closing Ceremony was pure gold. There is something magical that happens when you walk into an Olympic stadium. Goosebumps. These memorable performances, moments and emotions I felt during this night will stay with me forever. Those Olympic Rings are etched in my heart forever. I’m so proud of every Olympian of these Games, you guys did it! Goodness, I love the Olympics!!!!! #tokyo2020 #tokyoolympics #olympics #olympicspirit #paris2024 #closingceremony @dressthepopulation @olympics
